## The Bet

This is a bet on a specific, testable claim:

**For code generation tasks where the scope and files are known in advance, a system built on constrained attention will produce equivalent-quality code at a fraction of the cost, with higher consistency, than an open-ended agentic loop.**

The data supports the claim. 49/49 single-file exercises at 14.9x fewer tokens. 100% multi-file pass rates at 16-29x fewer tokens (21x average). 3-5% token variance versus 59%.

But benchmarks are controlled environments. Your codebase, your tasks, your expectations are the real test.

We are not asking you to trust the numbers. We are asking you to generate your own.

